      "text": [
        " اَلْمُعْتَكِفَةِ إِذَا طَمِثَتْ قَالَ «تَرْجِعُ إِلَى بَيْتِهَا فَإِذَا طَهُرَتْ رَجَعَتْ فَقَضَتْ مَا عَلَيْهَا »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2106 - It is narrated by Ibn Mahbub, from Abu Ayyub, from Abu Basir, from Abu Abdullah (as), regarding a woman performing i'tikaf who experiences menstruation.\nImam (as) said: \"She should return to her home, and when she becomes pure, she should return and make up for what she missed.\""
        ]
      }
    },
